==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''intellegentia'', '''intelligence''' (''intellegentia'' comes from ''inter-lege-nt-ia'', literally ''between-read-ing'', i.e., reading between the lines).

===Noun===
'''intelligence'''
# Capacity to [[understand]] and [[comprehend]].
# Capacity to [[solve]] problems.

====Synonyms====
*[[Wit]]
*[[Intellect]]
*[[Brightness]]

